[[File:List of international presidential trips made by Emmanuel Macron.svg|thumb|380px|Map of international trips made by Emmanuel Macron as president: {{legend|#a1a7ef|1 visit}} {{legend|#737ce8|2 visits}} <!-- {{legend|#4f5ae3|3 visits}} --> {{legend|#2533dd|4 visits}} {{legend|#1a25ac|5 visits}} <!-- {{legend|#111976|6 visits}} {{legend|#050725|7 or more visits}} --> {{legend|#000000|France and Andorra}}]] This is a '''list of international presidential trips made by Emmanuel Macron''', the [[List of Presidents of France|25th]] and current [[President of France|President]] of [[France]]. As of {{Monthyear}}, [[Emmanuel Macron]] has made 73 presidential trips to 43 states internationally since his [[French presidential inauguration|inauguration on 14 May 2017]]. [[List of presidential trips made by Emmanuel Macron|National trips]] are not included. The number of visits per country where he travelled are: * One visit to [[Algeria]], [[Argentina]], [[Armenia]], [[Australia]], [[Burkina Faso]], [[Canada]], [[China]], [[Côte d'Ivoire]], [[Czech Republic]], [[Denmark]], [[Estonia]], [[Finland]], [[Ghana]], [[Greece]], [[India]], [[Mauritania]], [[Netherlands]], [[Niger]], [[Nigeria]], [[Portugal]], [[Qatar]], [[Romania]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Senegal]], [[Slovakia]], [[Spain]], [[Sweden]], [[Tunisia]], [[Turkey]], [[United Arab Emirates]], [[United Kingdom]] and [[Vatican City]]. * Two visits to [[Austria]], [[Bulgaria]], [[Luxembourg]], [[Mali]], [[Morocco]] and [[Switzerland]]. * Three visits to [[Italy]], [[Russia]] and [[United States]]. * Nine visits to [[Germany]]. * Eleven visits to [[Belgium]].
== 2017 == {{main|List of presidential trips made by Emmanuel Macron}} [[File:G7 Taormina Paolo Gentiloni Emmanuel Macron handshake 2017-05-26 (cropped).jpg|thumb|President Emmanuel Macron meets with Italian Prime Minister [[Paolo Gentiloni]] at the [[43rd G7 summit]] in [[Taormina]], 26 May 2017]] The following are the international trips made by the President in 2017: {| class="wikitable sortable outercollapse" style="margin: 1em auto 1em auto" |- ! width=120|Country ! width=100|Areas visited ! width=90|Date(s) ! width=550 class=unsortable|Details |- | {{flag|Germany}} | [[Berlin]] | {{sort|2017-05-15|15 May}} | Macron's [[state visit]] to [[Germany]] was his first international trip as president. He chose Germany as the first foreign trip of his presidency in a demonstration of a pro-European sign, as well as to follow the tradition of French presidents making their first international trip to Germany.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Seibt|first1=Sébastian|title=Emmanuel Macron rencontrera la chancelière allemande Angela Merkel au lendemain de son investiture|url=http://www.france24.com/fr/20170512-emmanuel-macron-rencontre-allemagne-angela-merkel-investiture-politique|accessdate=16 May 2017|publisher=[[France 24]]|date=12 May 2017|language=French}}</ref> During his first full day in office, Macron met with German Chancellor [[Angela Merkel]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Saeed|first1=Saim|title=Macron to visit Berlin in first trip as French president|url=http://www.politico.eu/article/macron-to-visit-berlin-in-first-trip-as-french-president/|accessdate=14 May 2017|work=[[Politico]]|date=12 May 2017}}</ref> The two leaders agreed to construct a plan to reform the [[European Union]] amidst the rise of [[right-wing populism]] and [[Euroscepticism]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Macron pledges ‘profound’ EU reforms on first official visit to Berlin|url=http://www.france24.com/en/20170515-macron-first-visit-merkel-france-germany-profound-european-union-reforms|accessdate=16 May 2017|agency=[[Agence France-Presse]]|via=[[France 24]]|date=16 May 2017}}</ref> |- | {{flag|Mali}} | [[Gao]] | {{sort|2017-05-19|19 May}} | Macron met with [[French Armed Forces|French troops]] committed to [[Operation Barkhane]]. This was his first trip outside Europe as president.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.africanews.com/2017/05/15/president-macron-s-first-african-trip-set-to-visit-french-troops-in-mali/|title=President Macron's first African trip: set to visit French troops in Mali|date=16 May 2017|publisher=[[Africanews]]|author1=Abdur Rahman Alfa Shaban|accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref> |- | {{flag|Belgium}} | [[Brussels]] | {{sort|2017-05-25|25–26 May}} | Macron attended the [[2017 Brussels summit|NATO summit]], his first summit meeting as president. He held separate bilateral meetings with other heads of government, including U.S. President [[Donald Trump]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Trump to meet French President-elect Emmanuel Macron on May 25 at NATO Summit|url=http://www.financialexpress.com/world-news/trump-to-meet-french-president-elect-emmanuel-macron-on-may-25-at-nato-summit/660437/|accessdate=22 May 2017|agency=[[Asian News International]]|via=''[[The Financial Express (India)|The Financial Express]]''|date=9 May 2017}}</ref> |- | {{flag|Italy}} | [[Taormina]] | {{sort|2017-05-26|26–27 May}} | Macron attended the [[43rd G7 summit|G7 summit]] in Taormina.<ref>{{cite news|title=France's Macron hosts Italy's Gentiloni ahead of G7 meeting|url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/frances-macron-hosts-italys-gentiloni-ahead-g7-meeting-47546635|accessdate=22 May 2017|agency=[[Associated Press]]|via=[[ABC News]]|date=21 May 2017}}</ref> He held separate bilateral meetings with other heads of government, including British Prime Minister [[Theresa May]], Canadian Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]] and Japanese Prime Minister [[Shinzō Abe]]. |- |{{Flagicon|Morocco}} [[Morocco]] |[[Rabat]] |{{sort|2017-06-14|14–15 June}} |Macron met the King of Morocco [[Mohammed VI of Morocco|Mohammed VI]] during this private and friendly trip.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ouest-france.fr/monde/maroc/macron-au-maroc-l-amitie-dans-un-contexte-particulier-5061245|title=Macron au Maroc, l’amitié dans un contexte particulier|work=Ouest-France.fr|access-date=2017-06-15|language=fr-FR}}</ref> |- |{{flag|Belgium}} |[[Brussels]] |{{sort|2017-06-22|22–23 June}} |Macron attended in his first [[European Council]]. He held separate bilateral meetings with [[Angela Merkel]], and the representants of the [[Visegrád Group]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elysee.fr/Agenda/index/6/agenda-de-m-le-president-de-la-republique-du-lundi-19-juin-au-dimanche-25-juin-2017|title=Agenda de M. le président de la République du lundi 19 juin au dimanche 25 juin 2017|last=République|first=Présidence de la|work=www.elysee.fr|access-date=2017-06-22|language=fr-FR}}</ref> |- | {{flag|Germany}} | [[Berlin]] | {{sort|2017-06-29|29 June}} | Macron met with other European heads of state and government, as part of the preparations for the [[2017 G20 Hamburg summit|G20 summit]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Merkel, Macron to defend Paris climate accord at Hamburg G20 after US exit|url=https://www.efe.com/efe/english/world/merkel-macron-to-defend-paris-climate-accord-at-hamburg-g20-after-us-exit/50000262-3311719|accessdate=1 July 2017|agency=[[EFE]]|date=29 June 2017}}</ref> |- | {{flag|Mali}} | [[Bamako]] | {{sort|2017-07-02|2 July}} | Macron attends a security summit of the [[G5 Sahel]] to boost support for the creation of a regional counter-terror force.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.france24.com/en/20170630-macron-mali-g5-barkhane-al-qaeda-boko-haram-terrorism|title=France's Macron returns to Mali to boost regional anti-terrorism force|date=1 July 2017|publisher=[[France24]]|accessdate=2 July 2017}}</ref> |- | {{flag|Germany}} | [[Hamburg]] | {{sort|2017-07-07|7–8 July}} | Macron attended in the [[2017 G20 Hamburg summit|G20 summit]] in Hamburg. He held separate bilateral meetings with other heads of government, including Canadian Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]], Russian President [[Vladimir Putin]], and with German Chancellor [[Angela Merkel]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dw.com/en/g20-underway-in-hamburg-amid-violent-protests-live-updates/a-39589687|title=G20 underway in Hamburg amid violent protests|date=7 July 2017|publisher=[[Deutsche Welle]]|accessdate=7 July 2017}}</ref> |- |{{Flagicon|Switzerland}} [[Switzerland]] |[[Lausanne]] |10–11 July |Macron travelled to [[Lausanne]] to visit the [[International Olympic Committee]] for the presentation of the [[Paris bid for the 2024 Summer Olympics]]. During this trip Macron was accompanied by his wife [[Brigitte Macron|Brigitte,]] the [[Mayor of Paris]] [[Anne Hidalgo]] and the chairs of the bid, [[Bernard Lapasset]] and [[Tony Estanguet]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/sports/paris-2024-a-lausanne-devant-le-cio-macron-veut-frapper-fort-10-07-2017-7122555.php|title=Paris 2024 : à Lausanne, devant le CIO, Macron veut frapper fort|date=2017-07-10|work=leparisien.fr|language=fr|access-date=2017-07-10}}</ref> |- |{{flag|Italy}} |[[Trieste]] |12–13 July |Macron attended in the [[2017 Western Balkans Summit, Trieste|2017 Western Balkans Summit.]] One day before, he met German Chancellor [[Angela Merkel]] and Italian Prime Minister [[Paolo Gentiloni]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.rfi.fr/europe/20170712-ouverture-sommet-presidentiel-trieste-balkans|title=Ouverture du sommet présidentiel de Trieste sur les Balkans|date=2017-07-12|work=RFI|access-date=2017-07-12|language=fr-FR}}</ref> |- |{{Flag|Austria}} |[[Salzburg]] |23 August |Macron met Austrian Chancellor.<ref>https%3A%2F%2Fkurier.at%2Fpolitik%2Finland%2Fsalzburger-sozialgipfel-die-macrons-zu-gast-bei-den-kerns%2F282.223.776&usg=AFQjCNGBAOWqX5j6ZOTcD7JyfKjhCaTg_Q</ref> |- |{{Flag|Romania}} |[[Bucarest]] |24 August |Macron met Romanian president.<ref>http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ouest-france.fr%2Fpolitique%2Femmanuel-macron%2Fbucarest-macron-explique-que-les-francais-detestent-les-reformes-5203573&usg=AFQjCNG6_Mgg7gJ_CWmuN2CEo2h0t-296g</ref> |- |{{Flag|Bulgaria}} |[[Varna]] |25 August |Macron met Bulgarian President and Prime Minister in [[Euxinograd|Euxinograd Palace]].<ref>http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lexpress.fr%2Factualites%2F1%2Fpolitique%2Fmacron-la-pologne-se-met-en-marge-de-l-ue-sur-de-nombreux-sujets_1937694.html&usg=AFQjCNGGT0p1zn2Pi2wzrTrNaPYCAc9cPw</ref> |- |{{Flagicon|Luxembourg}} [[Luxembourg]] |[[Luxembourg City]], [[Niederanven]] |28 August |Macron meet [[Grand Duke Henri]] and [[Grand Duchess Maria Teresa of Luxembourg]]. Then there are political talks at [[Senningen Castle]] with the head of government [[Xavier Bettel]] and then Belgian Prime Minister [[Charles Michel]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.republicain-lorrain.fr/politique/2017/08/29/grands-defis-au-grand-duche|title=Visite présidentielle de Macron au Luxembourg : grands défis au Grand-Duché|access-date=2017-09-13|language=fr}}</ref> |- |{{Flag|Greece}} |[[Athens]] |6–7 September |Macron paid a state visit in Greece where he called to rebuild European Union.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/07/world/europe/emmanuel-macron-greece-european-union.html|title=Emmanuel Macron, in Greece, Calls for ‘Rebuilding’ E.U.|access-date=2017-09-12|publisher=[[New York Times]]}}</ref> |- |{{Flag|United States}} |[[New York City|New York]] |18–20 September |Macron participates to the 72th Session of the [[United Nations General Assembly]] and meet several head of states.<ref>https://franceintheus.org/spip.php?article8304</ref> |- |{{Flag|Estonia}} |[[Tallinn]], [[Tapa Army Base]] |28–29 September |Macron attended the EU Digital Summit and held a bilateral meeting with German Chancellor [[Angela Merkel]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/world/860220/merkel-macron-european-union-reforms-tallinn-meeting-estonia-summit|title=Merkel and Macron’s EU TAKEOVER: German head urges ‘INTENSE’ co-operation as she cosies up|acces