et with President [[Donald Trump]]. Official State Visit. |- | {{flag|Australia}} | [[Sydney]] | {{sort|2018-05-01|1–3 May}} | Macron met with Prime Minister [[Malcolm Turnbull]]. |- | {{flag|Germany}} | [[Aachen]] | {{sort|2018-05-09|9–10 May}} | Macron received the [[Charlemagne Prize]]. |- | {{flag|Bulgaria}} | [[Sofia]] | {{sort|2018-05-16|16–17 May}} | Macron attended the EU-Western Balkans summit. |- | {{flag|Russia}} | [[Saint Petersburg]] | {{sort|2018-05-24|24–25 May}} | Macron met with President [[Vladimir Putin]]. He also attended the [[St. Petersburg International Economic Forum]]. |- | {{flag|Canada}} | [[Ottawa]], [[Montreal]], [[La Malbaie]] | {{sort|2018-06-06|6–9 June}} | Macron met with Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]] in Ottawa and Premier of Quebec [[Philippe Couillard]] in Montreal. Macron also attended the [[44th G7 summit|G7 summit]] in La Malbaie. He held separate bilateral meetings with other heads of government, including British Prime Minister [[Theresa May]], German Chancellor [[Angela Merkel]], Italian Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] and U.S. President [[Donald Trump]]. |- | {{flag|Germany}} | [[Gransee]] | {{sort|2018-06-19|19 June}} | Macron met with Chancellor [[Angela Merkel]]. |- | {{flag|Vatican City}} | [[Vatican City]] | {{sort|2018-06-26|26 June}} | Macron met with [[Pope Francis]]. |- | {{Flag|Belgium}} | [[Brussels]] | {{sort|2018-06-28|28–29 June}} | Macron attended the [[European Council]]. |- | {{Flag|Mauritania}} | [[Nouakchott]] | {{sort|2018-07-02|2 July}} | Macron attended the 31st [[African Union]] summit. |- | {{Flag|Nigeria}} | [[Abuja]], [[Lagos]] | {{sort|2018-07-03|3–4 July}} | Macron met with President [[Muhammadu Buhari]]. |- | {{Flag|Russia}} | [[Saint Petersburg]] | {{sort|2018-07-10|10 July}} | Macron attended the semi-final between France and Belgium of the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]. |- | {{Flag|Belgium}} | [[Brussels]] | {{sort|2017-07-11|11–12 July}} | Macron attended the [[2018 Brussels summit|NATO summi