 attend the [[Organisation internationale de la Francophonie#Summits|Francophonie Summit]]. |- | {{Flag|Belgium}} | [[Brussels]] | {{sort|2018-10-10|17–19 October}} | Macron travelled to [[Brussels]] to attend a [[European Council]] and the 12th [[Asia-Europe Meeting]] (ASEM). |- | {{flag|Slovakia}} | [[Bratislava]] | {{sort|2018-10-26|26 October}} | Macron met with President [[Andrej Kiska]] and Prime Minister [[Peter Pellegrini]]. |- | {{flag|Czech Republic}} | [[Prague]] | {{sort|2018-10-26|26–27 October}} | Macron met with President [[Milos Zeman]] and Prime Minister [[Andrej Babis]]. |- | {{flag|Turkey}} | [[Istanbul]] | {{sort|2018-10-27|27 October}} | Macron attended a summit hosted by President [[Recep Tayyip Erdoğan]] on Syria conflict along with German Chancellor [[Angela Merkel]] and Russian President [[Vladimir Putin]]. |- | {{Flag|Morocco}} | [[Tangier]], [[Rabat]] | {{sort|2018-11-15|15 November}} | Macron travelled to [[Morocco]] to inaugurate along with King [[Mohammed VI]] the first [[high-speed railway line]] in Africa. |- | {{flag|Germany}} | [[Berlin]] | {{sort|2018-11-18|18 November}} | Macron travelled to [[Berlin]] to commemorate [[Volkstrauertag]] along with Chancellor [[Angela Merkel]] and President [[Frank-Walter Steinmeier]] at the [[Neue Wache]]. He also made a speech at the [[Bundestag]] about the [[European Union]]. |- | {{flag|Belgium}} | [[Brussels]], [[Ghent]], [[Molenbeek]], [[Louvain-la-Neuve]] | {{sort|2018-11-19|19–20 November}} | Macron paid a state visit to Belgium. He met with King [[Philippe of Belgium]] and Prime Minister [[Charles Michel]]. |- | {{flag|Belgium}} | [[Brussels]] | {{sort|2018-11-25|25 November}} | Macron attended an extraordinary summit on [[Brexit]] along with the other [[European Union]] leaders. |- | {{flag|Argentina}} | [[Buenos Aires]] | {{sort|2018-11-28|28 November – 1 December}} | Macron met with President [[Mauricio Macri]] in Buenos Aires. Macron also attended the [[2018 G20 Buenos Aires summit|G20 summit]] in Buenos Aires. He held separate bilateral meetings with other heads of government, including Australian Prime Minister [[Scott Morrison]], Canadian Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]], Chinese President [[Xi Jinping]], Japanese Prime Minister [[Shinzō Abe]], South African President [[Cyril Ramaphosa]] and Russian President [[Vladimir Putin]]. |}
== Future trips == === 2019 === {| class="wikitable sortable outercollapse" style="margin: 1em auto 1em auto" !''Department''/Country !Areas visited !width=80|Date(s) !Details |- | {{flag|Japan}} | [[Osaka]] | {{sort|2019-06-28|28–29 June}} | Macron is scheduled to attend the [[2019 G20 Osaka summit]]. |- | {{flag|Belgium}} | [[Brussels]] | {{sort|2019-07-22|22 July}} | Macron is scheduled to attend the [[2019 Brussels summit|NATO summit]]. |}
During the visit of the [[Prime Minister of Israel]], [[Benjamin Netanyahu]], to [[Paris]] on July 16, 2017, Macron said that he would visit his counterpart in [[Israel]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.lepoint.fr/politique/israel-palestine-macron-appelle-a-une-reprise-des-negociations-en-vue-d-une-solution-a-deux-etats-16-07-2017-2143533_20.php|title=Israël-Palestine : Macron appelle à une "reprise des négociations" en vue d'"une solution à deux États"|last=magazine|first=Le Point,|date=2017-07-16|work=Le Point|access-date=2017-07-16|language=fr-FR}}</ref>
During the visit of the [[President of Guatemala]], [[Jimmy Morales]], to Paris on June 8, 2017, Macron said that he would visit his counterpart in [[Guatemala]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.france24.com/en/20170608-guatemala-ratify-oecd-tax-convention-macronp|title=Macron and Morales visit|last=france24|first=france24|date=2017-06-08|work=france|access-date=2017-06-08|language=fr-FR}}</ref>
On 18 July 2018, during a press conference with Serbia's president [[Aleksandar Vučić]], President Macron confirmed he would pay a visit to [[Serbia]] later that year, possibly for [[Armistice Day]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.balkaneu.com/vucic-has-pestered-macron-in-order-to-persuade-him-to-visit-serbia-later-in-the-year/|title=Vucic has 'pestered' Macron in order to persuade him to visit Serbia later in the year|website=Independent Balkan News Agency|access-date=2018-07-18}}</ref>
